<Base title="Project Rescue" description="Project rescue – often also the rescue of major investments. Shopware 6 development by Hob by Horse.">
<div class="lp"><section class="hero"><div class="hi">
<p class="kicker">E-Commerce</p>
<h1>Project Rescue – Often Also the Rescue of Major Investments</h1>
<p>Automated processes in e-commerce are carried out as projects. Every project is intended to be led to success through the teamwork of various responsibilities. With many project participants, however, errors in some project phases can prevent the project goal from being achieved. In such cases, the developments of Hob by Horse can rescue many a project and bring the already achieved milestones together towards the longed-for end goal.</p>
</div></section>
<div class="content">
<h2>Project Rescue by Hob by Horse with Features in Shopware 6</h2>
<p>Project rescue means that through thorough analysis, the previous project is examined and investigated for errors. Sometimes only a single point is missing, sometimes project participants proceeded from false assumptions for their part of the project development. Through the objective, because uninvolved, external perspective, Hob by Horse recognises even the smallest details that are currently leading to project stagnation. You no longer need to discard or restart your project.</p>

<h2>Contents and Process of Project Rescue</h2>
<p>The first solution approach for project rescue already lies in unclear requirements and inadequate formulations. Whether these causes or a still-outstanding end-to-end review are causing the project to stall, Hob by Horse determines in the analysis. Subsequently, we proceed as follows for the rescue:</p>
<ul>
<li>We scrutinise the potentially conflict-ridden project culture, budget and time overruns, compliance with or absence of cooperation obligations, and lack of transparency in project progress. This allows us to identify the danger zone and narrow it down.</li>
<li>We communicate identified problems and our solution proposals with those responsible, with the aim of obtaining permission to continue the project. For this, we present our solution ideas for project rescue with Shopware 6.</li>
<li>The next rescue step consists of securing previous project progress in such a way that it can be continued with our solution ideas.</li>
</ul>
<p>This initially averts the failure of your project. As we continue towards success, we remain constantly by your side as a solution partner.</p>

<h2>Relevant Industries for a Project Rescue</h2>
<p>Project problems affect all economically oriented industries, with those at the corporate level being more affected than smaller medium-sized businesses. Fashion, lifestyle, food, research, aerospace — the list is as long as the German economic infrastructure. Of course, it makes sense to think about a project rescue when the project has already consumed a considerable budget. But there is no reason not to use our help for small projects and small budgets.</p>

<h2>Benefits of Project Rescue by Hob by Horse for Your Target Groups</h2>
<p>Target groups for successfully market-launched projects are either specialist customers from the B2B sector or B2C customers. These can be organisations, user structures or private individuals. What matters is that they all benefit from the rescued project, either through innovative products or services with high, forward-looking industry relevance. At best, through our service you not only rescue the investments made so far, but can also submit the project for EU funding with a promising prospect of success.</p>
<p>Don't know how to proceed, want to avoid a necessary project rescue, or commission one in good time before a possible failure? Hob by Horse looks forward to your call and responds promptly to your email!</p>
</div></div>
